05:37.013 --> 05:38.630
When am I going to be released, sir?

05:38.681 --> 05:40.566
You think you're going home, captain?

05:40.600 --> 05:41.933
I'm no longer a threat.

05:41.968 --> 05:43.969
I'm not connected to that rock anymore.

05:43.971 --> 05:48.557
That may be true, but...
We have other considerations.

05:48.608 --> 05:51.059
What considerations, sir?

05:51.110 --> 05:54.913
We need to find out exactly
what we're facing here.

05:54.947 --> 05:56.946
It seems you're the closest
thing to an expert we've got.

05:56.949 --> 05:59.067
I told you everything I know.

05:59.118 --> 06:00.786
We believe there may be
physiological aspects

06:00.820 --> 06:02.404
within your nervous system

06:02.455 --> 06:05.574
that allowed the enemy
to communicate with you.

06:05.625 --> 06:09.244
You've interacted with the rock
on two separate occasions.

06:09.295 --> 06:11.162
Sir, if you think
there's going to be a third...

06:11.164 --> 06:12.914
You're a United States
military officer, son.

06:12.965 --> 06:17.002
You're supposed to run
at the enemy, not away from him.

06:17.004 --> 06:20.038
When was the last time
<i>you</i> ran at the enemy, sir?

06:21.641 --> 06:27.095
Just so we're... we're clear on this...

06:27.146 --> 06:29.931
I have everything I need
to convince a court

06:29.982 --> 06:32.017
that you're a danger
to your country, captain.

06:32.068 --> 06:37.523
So, the way I see it,
you can do as you're ordered,

06:38.574 --> 06:40.659
report to the black site,

06:40.693 --> 06:43.495
help us learn everything we can

06:43.529 --> 06:46.498
about this thing we're up against...

06:46.532 --> 06:48.533
Or you can go to prison.

06:58.043 --> 07:00.628
- Mr. President.
- Mr. Lawrence.

07:00.679 --> 07:06.017
As I rode here, thinking
on this... Situation,

07:06.051 --> 07:09.888
I have never felt more acutely
the duty of the constitution,

07:09.890 --> 07:14.225
that which I swore to defend.

07:14.227 --> 07:18.229
Do you know the passage from the preamble?

07:18.231 --> 07:20.565
"We the people..."

07:20.567 --> 07:24.902
In order to secure the blessings of liberty

07:24.904 --> 07:28.606
"to ourselves and our posterity..."

07:28.640 --> 07:33.611
That's our descendants,
Mr. Lawrence... our children.

07:35.381 --> 07:38.783
And that's on me now.

07:38.817 --> 07:41.953
If I may, sir, you're not alone.

07:44.056 --> 07:47.508
It's <i> "we</i> the people."

07:47.559 --> 07:53.358
And we are right here... With you... Ready.

08:02.507 --> 08:04.809
Protect this rock.

08:04.843 --> 08:07.778
That's my decision.

08:12.715 --> 08:15.383
[Cellphone vibrating]

08:17.970 --> 08:21.273
- [Beep]
- Hi, mom.

08:23.976 --> 08:25.360
I don't know.

08:25.394 --> 08:28.113
They hauled him away last night
before I could even talk to him.

08:31.651 --> 08:34.953
He said...

08:34.986 --> 08:37.455
He said he remembers.

08:40.493 --> 08:42.626
Everything.

08:45.998 --> 08:47.982
Thanks.

08:48.017 --> 08:49.818
I love you, too.

08:49.852 --> 08:53.471
Bye.

08:53.506 --> 08:55.490
[Sighs]

08:55.524 --> 08:58.092
- [Door opens]
- Henry: Daddy!

08:58.094 --> 09:00.662
Sean: Hello, Henry. [Chuckles] My God.

09:02.398 --> 09:04.849
So, you remember me?

09:04.900 --> 09:07.018
Of course I do.

09:07.069 --> 09:08.853
You're my son.

09:16.612 --> 09:19.747
[Sighs]

09:19.782 --> 09:21.332
Welcome home.

09:27.870 --> 09:30.572
Come on.

09:37.681 --> 09:40.182
This one is for the best hitter
in the playoffs.

09:40.184 --> 09:42.685
I'm so proud of you, little man.

09:42.687 --> 09:45.020
And here's the airplane you left me.

09:45.022 --> 09:47.356
I play with it all the time.

09:47.407 --> 09:49.024
Come on.

09:51.862 --> 09:55.614
And that's when mom took me
to see the Orioles.

09:55.665 --> 09:58.834
It was awesome.

10:02.372 --> 10:05.107
Dad, do you want to go out back
and play catch?

10:13.300 --> 10:16.185
Claire: I thought you...

10:16.219 --> 10:18.687
We didn't think you were coming back.

10:28.948 --> 10:32.117
Look at that. [Grunts]

10:35.205 --> 10:37.489
My daughter's favorite...

10:37.540 --> 10:40.826
some character from a television show.

10:40.877 --> 10:43.512
Can't believe she left it in the car.

10:43.546 --> 10:46.248
They've probably
torn the residence apart by now

10:46.282 --> 10:48.333
looking for it.

10:48.384 --> 10:50.002
[Chuckles]

10:54.724 --> 10:57.009
I've spent far too many hours
at the office...

10:58.978 --> 11:02.631
Not enough at the dinner table.

11:02.665 --> 11:04.766
There's nothing more important than family.

11:06.936 --> 11:09.187
When was the last time you saw yours?

11:10.823 --> 11:11.940
Minx: Ask another.

11:11.991 --> 11:15.360
Ask another! Drill wants you to.

11:15.411 --> 11:18.196
Um, okay.

11:18.247 --> 11:21.867
How do you travel from place to place?

11:21.918 --> 11:25.370
- [Electricity crackling]
- [Whispering]

11:25.421 --> 11:27.289
- [Gasps]
- [Chuckles]

11:27.340 --> 11:29.291
[Door closes]

11:35.464 --> 11:37.966
Lena?

11:37.968 --> 11:40.802
[Rattle in distance]

11:40.804 --> 11:43.805
Minx?

11:43.807 --> 11:46.975
Um, do you like it here?

11:47.026 --> 11:48.977
[Electricity humming]

11:53.199 --> 11:57.152
Are you s-staying a long time?

11:57.203 --> 12:00.989
[Whispering]

12:06.829 --> 12:09.164
- Sorry.
- [Gasps]

12:09.198 --> 12:10.832
Looks like I missed dinner.

12:10.834 --> 12:14.335
Drill said not to tell daddy
about the game.

12:14.337 --> 12:16.671
It has to be our secret.

12:16.673 --> 12:18.673
[Lid closes]

12:18.675 --> 12:21.342
That's okay, honey.
We're just glad you're home.

12:21.344 --> 12:22.777
[Smooches]

12:24.396 --> 12:25.947
Um, I'll heat something up.

12:25.981 --> 12:27.682
You go play with your daughter.

12:27.716 --> 12:28.850
Okay.

12:28.852 --> 12:33.851
So... What are we playing?

12:44.950 --> 12:48.870
He refused to go to sleep.

12:48.921 --> 12:50.905
"One more story, daddy, one more."

12:55.075 --> 12:57.810
He could hear me.

12:59.279 --> 13:02.081
[Chuckles] It was amazing.

13:02.115 --> 13:04.015
He can barely believe that you're back.

13:07.615 --> 13:09.082
Me, neither.

13:11.486 --> 13:12.953
Sean, we need...

13:12.987 --> 13:13.987
I'm tired.

13:14.038 --> 13:15.038
Claire...

13:15.936 --> 13:17.615
I haven't slept...

13:19.123 --> 13:21.815
Truly slept... in months.

13:26.301 --> 13:30.087
Yeah. Of course. [Breathes deeply]

13:32.006 --> 13:34.307
I wasn't sure if...

13:35.843 --> 13:37.844
I wasn't sure if you were sleeping...

13:40.181 --> 13:43.150
upstairs or if you...

13:43.184 --> 13:45.819
[Sighs]

13:45.853 --> 13:47.421
Are you sleeping upstairs?

13:49.240 --> 13:51.191
[Cellphone vibrating]

13:55.863 --> 13:57.697
Wes, I can't really talk right now.

13:57.699 --> 13:59.366
I know.

13:59.368 --> 14:03.036
I just... I just wanted to check in on you.

14:03.038 --> 14:04.371
[Door creaks]

14:04.405 --> 14:08.675
I'm fine. I am.

14:08.709 --> 14:11.044
So, he came back?

14:11.095 --> 14:14.297
Where else would he go? This is his home.

14:24.525 --> 14:25.892
Did you two talk?

14:25.926 --> 14:29.562
Uh, no. He was tired.

14:29.597 --> 14:31.231
[Sighs]

14:31.233 --> 14:34.734
And I'm not... I'm not really sure

14:34.769 --> 14:36.703
how this is supposed to work, Wes.

14:36.737 --> 14:37.904
Which part?

14:37.938 --> 14:39.706
All of it.

14:39.740 --> 14:40.907
Well, I...

14:40.958 --> 14:44.577
I think we just try
and figure it out day by day.

14:44.628 --> 14:47.413
- [Sighs]
- Listen, Claire...

14:47.415 --> 14:49.449
I... I just want you
to be careful around Sean.

14:49.483 --> 14:50.416
Wes...

14:50.467 --> 14:52.168
- Okay? I... I just...
- Wes.

14:52.219 --> 14:54.587
We don't really know... we don't
really know what he's been through,

14:54.638 --> 14:59.792
what it did to him,
what he's done, what he'll do.

14:59.827 --> 15:03.596
He's gonna be fine.

15:03.598 --> 15:05.265
We're...

15:05.267 --> 15:08.501
[Sighs] Gonna be fine.

15:10.537 --> 15:13.172
Just be careful, Claire.

15:36.096 --> 15:38.047
[Clicking]

15:53.880 --> 15:56.380
Cassandra, you left this in daddy's car.

15:56.480 --> 15:57.780
Oh, thank you, mommy.

15:57.814 --> 15:59.949
Mm-hmm. [Chuckles]

15:59.983 --> 16:02.118
Now, I couldn't find my phone.

16:02.152 --> 16:05.788
Uh, are you sure you put it in my purse?

16:05.822 --> 16:08.624
I think so.

16:08.658 --> 16:10.960
We'll check the residence tonight, ma'am.

16:10.994 --> 16:12.461
- Thank you.
- Goodnight.

16:12.496 --> 16:13.963
Goodnight, Cassandra.

16:13.997 --> 16:17.466
- Mm.
- [Door closes]

16:17.500 --> 16:20.636
[Smooches]

16:20.670 --> 16:22.805
Sweet dreams, honey.

16:25.976 --> 16:28.927
[Door opens, closes]

16:45.995 --> 16:48.947
[Electricity crackling]

16:52.969 --> 16:54.937
[Whispering]

16:56.666 --> 16:58.617
Dad!

17:01.265 --> 17:05.050
Dad, where are you?

17:05.102 --> 17:07.053
Sean: In the kitchen.

17:11.065 --> 17:12.065
What happened?

17:12.365 --> 17:15.065
You know, I couldn't find
where grammy left the griddle.

17:15.765 --> 17:18.468
Um, we haven't used it since...

17:19.865 --> 17:20.965
Since you were gone.

17:21.875 --> 17:23.992
- [Sizzling]
- Yeah, I know.

17:24.044 --> 17:27.329
But I made blueberry... your favorite.

17:31.551 --> 17:32.835
Aren't you having some?

17:32.886 --> 17:35.087
No, I'm gonna leave the rest
for you and your mom.

17:35.121 --> 17:39.424
But... I will sit with you.

17:52.822 --> 17:57.442
Henry, I want to talk to you
about something.

17:57.493 --> 18:00.112
You remember what daddy's job is, right?

18:00.163 --> 18:01.697
I protect people.

18:01.748 --> 18:04.199
People like you and mommy,

18:04.250 --> 18:06.168
other families around the country.

18:10.673 --> 18:12.791
Well, I have a new mission...

18:12.842 --> 18:18.171
A very important mission...
and I need your help.

18:19.966 --> 18:22.934
I need you to look out
for your mom while I'm gone.

18:22.969 --> 18:25.554
But you just got home.

18:27.140 --> 18:28.440
How can you leave again?

18:28.474 --> 18:30.442
I know, son.

18:32.812 --> 18:37.783
I need you to know
that I want to be here with you.

18:37.817 --> 18:39.117
Promise you're gonna come back.

18:39.152 --> 18:40.285
Henry...

18:40.319 --> 18:41.736
Promise!

18:43.956 --> 18:46.258
I promise.

18:48.661 --> 18:50.629
I don't believe you.

18:57.303 --> 18:59.587
Claire: You can't do this to him.

18:59.639 --> 19:01.589
You can't do this to Henry, Sean.

19:01.641 --> 19:03.258
Hey. Hey, stop.

19:03.309 --> 19:06.428
Hey, look at me. What is this about?

19:06.479 --> 19:07.479
- Is this ab...
- Wes Lawrence?

19:07.513 --> 19:09.848
Y... You think I care about Wes Lawrence?

19:09.899 --> 19:13.184
Then what <i>do</i> you care about?

19:13.235 --> 19:14.519
It sure as hell doesn't feel like it's us.

19:14.570 --> 19:16.521
Pentagon gave me two choices...

19:16.572 --> 19:19.774
Go to prison or become their guinea pig.

19:19.825 --> 19:21.443
- How are you even...
- Here?

19:21.494 --> 19:25.113
I told them I needed one night at home

19:25.164 --> 19:27.365
before I made a decision.
I don't understand.

19:27.416 --> 19:29.117
Which did you choose?

19:29.168 --> 19:31.085
The only one that protects our son.

19:33.339 --> 19:35.707
Sean.

19:35.758 --> 19:38.042
Sean.

19:40.763 --> 19:43.515
What are you going to do?

19:43.549 --> 19:45.583
What are we supposed to do,
lock our daughter in her room

19:45.618 --> 19:47.218
- and throw away the key?
- Of course not.

19:47.269 --> 19:49.554
I'm just saying maybe I should watch
what I say about work in case she's...

19:49.605 --> 19:51.055
In case what?

19:51.057 --> 19:52.223
In case she's still talking to Drill.

19:52.225 --> 19:55.059
Uh... Minx isn't dangerous, Wes.

19:55.110 --> 19:57.312
But her friend is.

19:57.363 --> 19:59.197
[Sighs]

19:59.231 --> 20:01.866
Look, you just need to trust me, okay?

20:01.900 --> 20:04.535
The less she knows, the safer she'll be.

20:04.570 --> 20:07.705
You think that's how to keep
us safe... keep us in the dark?

20:07.740 --> 20:11.542
We've discovered something, Lena.

20:11.577 --> 20:14.712
And believe me when I say
we are making progress.

20:14.746 --> 20:15.913
"Progress"?

20:15.915 --> 20:17.915
[Scoffing] That's all you're gonna tell me?

20:17.917 --> 20:19.383
I... I... I can't.

20:19.418 --> 20:21.002
[Sighs]

20:21.053 --> 20:22.670
Okay? We just need...

20:22.721 --> 20:25.006
You just to trust me a little while longer.

20:25.057 --> 20:26.090
Okay?

20:28.393 --> 20:31.345
You take care of everyone else.

20:31.396 --> 20:34.015
I can take care of our daughter.

20:34.066 --> 20:36.767
Sean: What do you hope to learn from me?

20:36.802 --> 20:38.769
I have spent my whole life posing questions

20:38.804 --> 20:40.938
about the universe, Captain Bennigan...

20:40.973 --> 20:43.941
about the possibility
of a higher intelligence

20:43.976 --> 20:45.943
somewhere out there.

20:45.978 --> 20:49.447
Because of you, I finally
get a chance to answer them.

20:49.449 --> 20:51.782
- A higher intelligence?
- [Beep]

20:51.784 --> 20:54.285
What little we've learned
about this rock so far,

20:54.319 --> 20:56.954
one thing is clear...
The being that created it...

20:56.956 --> 21:01.959
Compared to ants,<i> we</i> are
a higher intelligence, doctor.

21:02.010 --> 21:04.795
And I'm guessing we must have
seemed pretty intriguing to them

21:04.846 --> 21:06.430
until we invented bug spray.

21:06.465 --> 21:08.299
You really think you're the only one

21:08.350 --> 21:10.468
getting answers from this encounter?

21:10.519 --> 21:13.137
This visitor, he's getting them, too.

21:13.188 --> 21:14.221
About us.

21:14.272 --> 21:15.806
And just when he's learned

21:15.808 --> 21:19.143
precisely what it's gonna take
to destroy us,

21:19.145 --> 21:21.645
he's gonna use that "higher intelligence"

21:21.647 --> 21:24.982
to do exactly that.

21:25.033 --> 21:27.952
Unless you help me stop him.

21:34.958 --> 21:37.477
- [Knocking on door]
- Wes?

21:37.556 --> 21:39.323
Wes!

21:41.877 --> 21:44.161
I can't believe you'd do this,
that you would take Sean

21:44.212 --> 21:46.163
without even having the guts
to talk to me about it first.

21:46.214 --> 21:47.832
I didn't have any say in any of this.

21:47.834 --> 21:49.951
You sat there on the phone with me
last night, asking me questions...

21:50.033 --> 21:51.353
I don't... I don't agree
with how this was handled,

21:51.401 --> 21:53.319
but Sean is the only one with inside
information about this thing.

21:53.403 --> 21:55.654
He's a person, not some object

21:55.705 --> 21:58.491
for you to have
your scientist experiments on.

21:58.542 --> 22:00.159
They're your scientists, too, Claire.

22:00.210 --> 22:01.660
They work for all of us.

22:02.610 --> 22:05.112
This isn't some underground,
mercenary operation.

22:05.611 --> 22:07.245
This is the sovereign, federal government

22:07.280 --> 22:09.115
of the United States of America
trying to protect our children

22:09.180 --> 22:10.647
from a threat that we
don't fully understand.

22:10.682 --> 22:12.349
But Sean does, Wes.

22:12.351 --> 22:18.288
This thing has... been inside
our homes, with our children.

22:18.690 --> 22:22.159
We haven't been able to do
a damn thing to stop it.

22:22.193 --> 22:25.162
Maybe he's right.

22:25.196 --> 22:31.118
Maybe the only way to save us
is [sighs] to destroy that rock.

22:31.669 --> 22:34.538
Sean is clouded by
the trauma he has been through.

22:34.540 --> 22:36.840
His judgment is impaired.

22:36.874 --> 22:38.708
And yours isn't?

22:38.759 --> 22:41.044
Did he tell you this was about us?

22:42.546 --> 22:45.715
So are you sure that you're...
Seeing this clearly?

22:45.717 --> 22:46.933
Hmm?

22:48.552 --> 22:51.187
You were there with those children, Claire.

22:51.222 --> 22:52.472
You were in that room.

22:52.523 --> 22:54.307
You were willing to let
those children be guinea pigs.

22:54.358 --> 22:55.976
So are you honestly saying
that you would be here

22:56.027 --> 22:57.811
trying to justify what he has done

22:57.862 --> 22:59.229
if he was not your husband?

22:59.231 --> 23:03.149
You need to determine who you believe,

23:03.200 --> 23:05.151
who do you trust, because this is an enemy

23:05.202 --> 23:09.539
and we need to fight it using
whatever and whomever we have.

23:16.514 --> 23:18.631
At least let me see him.

23:20.918 --> 23:24.387
I didn't even get
to talk to him last night.

23:24.421 --> 23:26.089
We just found him, Wes.

23:26.091 --> 23:30.059
Who knows who long
they're gonna keep him there?

23:32.593 --> 23:36.493
All of this... Everything
that has happened to him...

23:36.767 --> 23:39.602
is because of me...

23:39.653 --> 23:42.105
Us.

23:42.156 --> 23:46.809
Let me see him. Let me talk him.

23:46.844 --> 23:48.161
I owe him that.

23:50.147 --> 23:52.749
You owe him that.

23:52.783 --> 23:58.043
Okay. I'll make a call.

24:01.175 --> 24:05.628
Okay.

24:05.679 --> 24:08.464
[Door opens, closes]

24:08.515 --> 24:10.216
Dr. Tully: What do you think you're doing?

24:10.267 --> 24:12.135
Just trying to talk to you.

24:12.186 --> 24:14.770
You're trying to scare me.

24:14.805 --> 24:16.105
Sometimes, the truth is scary.

24:16.140 --> 24:18.441
Do you think you're the first military man

24:18.475 --> 24:20.142
to suggest that any visitor to our planet

24:20.177 --> 24:21.310
would want to hurt us?

24:21.361 --> 24:24.647
No, but I'm trying not to be the last.

24:24.698 --> 24:27.817
Look, you can hook me up to the rock,

24:27.868 --> 24:30.152
take brain scans,
test every nerve in my body,

24:30.203 --> 24:31.654
but there's one thing your lab work

24:31.705 --> 24:33.656
will <i> never</i> be able to tell you.

24:33.707 --> 24:34.874
And what's that?

24:34.908 --> 24:37.660
What I saw in the blue light.

24:39.329 --> 24:42.665
You brought me here
to learn from me, doctor.

24:42.667 --> 24:44.333
So learn from me.

24:44.335 --> 24:47.735
- And how am I supposed to...
- Just ask.

24:48.555 --> 24:50.473
Ask me what I saw.

25:04.905 --> 25:06.522
Here.

25:06.573 --> 25:08.858
Jessup: So, you want to tell me

25:08.909 --> 25:11.026
why you need a tactical vest
to watch your son?

25:11.028 --> 25:13.963
After what we saw yesterday,
do you feel safe?

25:13.997 --> 25:15.698
Not even a little.

25:15.749 --> 25:18.467
But if this thing is what you say it is,

25:18.501 --> 25:19.785
then wearing a flak jacket

25:19.836 --> 25:21.704
ain't gonna make a damn bit of difference.

25:21.755 --> 25:23.539
Uh, Claire...

25:23.590 --> 25:25.341
You're a good partner, Jessup.

25:25.408 --> 25:28.510
Thank you.

25:28.545 --> 25:32.047
Look, just... Be careful, all right?

25:51.951 --> 25:53.952
[Alarm chirps]

26:19.595 --> 26:21.063
[ <i>Knock on door</i> ]

26:21.097 --> 26:24.066
Justus: <i> And who might this be? Hmm.</i>

26:25.601 --> 26:27.903
<i>Kylie! Come in! Come in!</i>

26:27.937 --> 26:31.239
<i>You're just in time</i>
<i>for this wonderful experiment.</i>

26:31.274 --> 26:33.075
Hey, Minx, I've got to go back to work.

26:33.109 --> 26:34.743
Kylie: <i>I lost my way, Justus.</i>

26:34.777 --> 26:37.245
<i>You... you know what I do when I'm lost?</i>

26:37.280 --> 26:39.781
<i>I use bread crumbs to find my way back.</i>

26:39.783 --> 26:40.916
Minx? I've got to go.

26:40.950 --> 26:43.084
<i>Just like, um, hansel and gretel.</i>

26:43.119 --> 26:45.253
Okay, daddy. Love you.

26:45.288 --> 26:47.422
<i>Ba-dum, ba-dum. It leaves a trail.</i>

26:47.457 --> 26:48.957
- Bye.
- <i>Here, you try.</i>

26:49.008 --> 26:51.960
I recognize that doll. Who is it?

26:52.011 --> 26:53.261
He's Justus. He's the best.

26:53.296 --> 26:55.931
Everyone watches his show.

26:55.965 --> 26:57.599
<i>Okay, everybody.</i>

26:57.633 --> 26:59.100
Why do <i>you</i> watch?

26:59.135 --> 27:00.769
<i>Join hands and help a friend.</i>

27:00.803 --> 27:02.771
- I don't know.
- <i>Get ready.</i>

27:02.805 --> 27:04.940
I guess 'cause he knows
how to talk to kids.

27:04.974 --> 27:06.641
<i>Oh, I almost forgot!</i>

27:06.692 --> 27:11.146
<i>Kids, check out my new Justus doll.</i>

27:11.148 --> 27:12.647
Doll: <i>Hi, I'm Justus.</i>

27:12.649 --> 27:15.317
<i>Now you can take</i>
<i>a little bit of justus with you</i>

27:15.319 --> 27:16.618
<i>wherever you go.</i>

27:16.652 --> 27:18.119
[Sighs]

27:18.154 --> 27:21.623
Okay. Bye, kiddo.

27:21.657 --> 27:24.125
I love you.

27:24.160 --> 27:25.960
Bye, daddy.

27:32.683 --> 27:33.933
Lena: No more games.

27:33.981 --> 27:37.800
Drill, I want you
to leave my daughter alone.

27:37.880 --> 27:39.247
Please.

27:39.298 --> 27:44.980
I'll do whatever it takes,
uh, whatever you want, just...

27:47.807 --> 27:50.091
Leave Minx out of it.

27:52.144 --> 27:53.595
Understand?

27:53.646 --> 27:56.932
<i>I'll make you an offer you can't refuse...</i>

27:56.983 --> 28:01.181
<i>One... Lolli... Pop... Each.</i>

28:03.823 --> 28:06.107
Corey: <i>But I can't choose!</i>

28:06.158 --> 28:07.359
<i>There's too many!</i>

28:07.361 --> 28:09.027
Mom!

28:09.078 --> 28:11.029
Is Drill here?

28:11.063 --> 28:12.530
I want to talk to him.

28:12.532 --> 28:14.115
About what?

28:14.166 --> 28:18.903
I... I need... I need him to do something.

28:21.507 --> 28:25.794
He's not here, mommy,
but we can ask him later.

28:25.845 --> 28:27.045
Where is he?

28:27.096 --> 28:30.298
He's with a new friend...
an important friend.

28:32.384 --> 28:35.220
Why is this new friend so important, Minx?

28:35.287 --> 28:38.139
Sean: Something terrible is coming.

28:38.190 --> 28:43.811
Before I crashed,
I felt something enter my mind,

28:43.863 --> 28:45.647
as if something was ripping it apart

28:45.698 --> 28:47.315
looking through my memories.

28:47.366 --> 28:51.986
And that's when I had my first vision...

28:52.037 --> 28:54.989
a vision of things to come.

28:55.040 --> 28:56.824
And what did you see?

28:56.875 --> 28:59.661
[Sighs]

28:59.712 --> 29:01.662
First, I was at my house.

29:01.714 --> 29:03.548
Door was open...

29:03.582 --> 29:05.500
I called out.

29:05.551 --> 29:09.387
No one answered. They were all gone.

29:09.421 --> 29:12.924
Then, all of a sudden,
I was at this playground.

29:12.926 --> 29:16.094
The swings were still swinging.
[ <i>Children laughing</i> ]

29:16.096 --> 29:18.262
The carousel was still spinning
around and around,

29:18.264 --> 29:20.098
as if the kids were just there.

29:20.100 --> 29:23.267
And again, I called out, "Is anyone here?"

29:23.269 --> 29:26.604
No one answered.

29:26.606 --> 29:28.206
Then I was at this school...

29:28.240 --> 29:29.524
[ <i>Bell rings</i> ]

29:29.575 --> 29:34.529
hallways, classrooms... all empty.

29:34.580 --> 29:37.865
But there were still shoes on the ground,

29:37.916 --> 29:40.284
backpacks still open,

29:40.335 --> 29:43.754
homework out, ready to be handed in.

29:43.789 --> 29:49.093
That's when I realized... It was all gone.

29:49.127 --> 29:51.362
Everyone was gone.

29:52.830 --> 29:54.765
Wes: Did she say
who the important friend was?

29:54.800 --> 29:56.767
No, just that this friend knows things...

29:56.802 --> 29:58.602
things that the other kids don't.

29:58.637 --> 30:00.636
With Drill, it's not about
the child. It never is.

30:00.936 --> 30:02.735
It's about who they
have access to... their parents.

30:02.736 --> 30:03.985
Well, do you know what he wants?

30:03.987 --> 30:05.737
Yeah, something
we're keeping hidden from him,

30:05.788 --> 30:07.071
something he can't get from Minx.

30:07.122 --> 30:09.157
Our computers are out of
the house, we won't discuss it.

30:09.208 --> 30:12.293
Who else knows where it is?

30:12.328 --> 30:14.829
Wes, what is it?

30:16.882 --> 30:18.499
- The doll.
- What doll?

30:18.550 --> 30:20.334
Look, the... s-s-she didn't just forget it.

30:20.386 --> 30:21.669
S... She left it there on purpose.

30:21.720 --> 30:24.672
[Tires screeching]

30:24.723 --> 30:27.342
[Engine revs]

30:28.321 --> 30:29.572
First lady: Her room is right there, but...

30:29.620 --> 30:30.536
Mr. Lawrence,
how could my daughter's room...

30:30.620 --> 30:32.287
Wes: The entity uses children, sir.

30:32.420 --> 30:34.887
That doll was in your car
yesterday afternoon.

30:34.921 --> 30:38.891
If... if... if there's
a tracking device inside it...

30:40.677 --> 30:42.010
It's okay, sweetheart.

30:42.061 --> 30:43.595
This gentleman's just trying
to make sure everyone's safe.

30:43.597 --> 30:45.681
The voice box that was inside here.
Did you take it out, Cassandra?

30:45.732 --> 30:47.766
- Did you move it somewhere?
- Mommy?

30:47.817 --> 30:49.768
- Did you put it somewhere?
- I think we should calm down.

30:49.770 --> 30:50.936
- Cassandra?
- Okay, Mr. Lawrence...

30:50.938 --> 30:52.771
The voice box that was
in here... did you move it?

30:52.773 --> 30:55.657
[Electricity crackling]

30:59.779 --> 31:01.747
Come here, sweetheart.

31:01.781 --> 31:05.083
[Vibrating]

31:20.800 --> 31:24.269
[Cellphone vibrating]

31:26.022 --> 31:28.106
Is that mommy's phone, Cassandra?

31:28.141 --> 31:30.442
You told me you put it
back in my purse, sweetie.

31:30.476 --> 31:31.943
We've been looking everywhere.

31:31.978 --> 31:33.645
I was just trying to help my friend.

31:33.647 --> 31:36.148
It's an app for tracking your route.

31:36.150 --> 31:37.983
He knows where the rock is.

31:38.034 --> 31:40.485
[Electricity crackling]

31:40.536 --> 31:42.020
Dr. Tully: I don't understand.

31:42.054 --> 31:45.690
This being also restored
your son's hearing.

31:45.725 --> 31:48.827
It brought another woman out of a coma.

31:48.878 --> 31:50.495
If he could manipulate that
to help someone,

31:50.546 --> 31:52.497
he could do it to hurt someone.

31:52.548 --> 31:54.833
Why not just stop our hearts?

31:54.884 --> 31:57.335
If he's the enemy like you say...

31:59.388 --> 32:01.339
why not kill us all?

32:01.390 --> 32:04.843
Maybe he has other plans for us.

32:04.877 --> 32:07.012
Cassandra: He needed my help, daddy.

32:07.096 --> 32:09.180
- What for, sweetheart?
- To call home.

32:09.231 --> 32:15.186
The rock... It isn't, uh,
a... A ship, it's not a bomb...

32:15.237 --> 32:16.771
It's a phone.

32:18.991 --> 32:20.275
What does it need a phone for?

32:20.326 --> 32:23.111
To send a signal.

32:23.162 --> 32:25.997
He's calling for reinforcements.

32:29.701 --> 32:33.003
My visit was cleared
by Wes Lawrence at the D.O.D.

32:33.038 --> 32:35.372
Just a moment, please.

32:39.544 --> 32:40.844
[Dialing]

32:40.879 --> 32:44.014
I have a Claire Bennigan at Station 2.

32:44.049 --> 32:45.215
Clearance check.

32:45.266 --> 32:47.718
[Cellphone vibrating]

32:49.604 --> 32:51.522
Wes: Claire, you need to get out of there.

32:51.556 --> 32:52.723
Call me when you get this.

32:52.725 --> 32:54.525
Drill knows where the rock is!
Get out of there now!

32:59.063 --> 33:02.699
Agent Bennigan, I'm gonna need
you to do something for me.

33:04.452 --> 33:06.737
Yes?

33:06.788 --> 33:09.072
When you leave the facility,

33:09.123 --> 33:11.909
I'll need you to report back
here for a standard debriefing.

33:11.911 --> 33:14.645
- Is that understood?
- Of course.

33:22.804 --> 33:27.758
Agent Bennigan... she wanted me
to bring her a bulletproof vest.

33:27.809 --> 33:30.427
- Any idea why?
- No.

33:30.478 --> 33:33.063
I tried to follow her,
but I lost her on the I-170.

33:33.097 --> 33:35.065
- I-170?
- Yeah.

33:35.099 --> 33:38.268
I know where she's going.

33:38.270 --> 33:39.936
He's right through here.

33:39.938 --> 33:41.605
I didn't think you'd make it.

33:41.607 --> 33:44.241
I had to lie to Wes,
but I got what you needed.

33:44.275 --> 33:46.827
[Velcro ripping]

33:54.952 --> 33:55.919
She's with us.

33:55.953 --> 33:57.754
How can you trust her?

33:57.788 --> 34:00.423
Hasn't she been running experiments?

34:00.458 --> 34:03.627
Look, do either of you have
any real clue how to do this?

34:03.629 --> 34:05.629
Sean: We're gonna reverse
the electromagnetic field

34:05.680 --> 34:08.632
around the rock, creating an E.M.P.

34:08.683 --> 34:11.301
Okay, but we also need something
to fire the device...

34:11.351 --> 34:12.969
a small electronic receiver.

34:13.020 --> 34:14.187
I got that covered.

34:15.473 --> 34:18.391
It's got a powerful switch,
good range of signal.

34:18.442 --> 34:20.310
We'll be clear before the blast happens.

34:20.360 --> 34:21.811
Put this on.

34:21.813 --> 34:25.815
I will find something
to cut the monitor off his leg.

34:25.817 --> 34:27.817
[Electricity crackling]

34:30.925 --> 34:33.623
I need this room completely cleared.

34:33.657 --> 34:37.460
Stand post outside the doors.
No one gets in.

34:37.495 --> 34:38.962
Dr. Tully, are you sure?

34:38.996 --> 34:40.295
I'll be fine. Thank you.

34:40.331 --> 34:41.965
- Now.
- Yes, ma'am.

34:41.998 --> 34:43.466
Let's move.

34:49.090 --> 34:52.225
[Sighs] We need to hurry.

34:52.259 --> 34:55.061
Each tower has four magnets.

34:55.094 --> 34:58.898
The magnets are attached
to two wires... live and ground.

34:58.933 --> 35:00.233
Unhook all the wires,

35:00.267 --> 35:02.735
then turn the magnet towards the rock.

35:02.770 --> 35:04.487
We need to do this
for each and every magnet.

35:04.521 --> 35:05.488
And then what happens?

35:05.522 --> 35:07.240
The magnetic shield will be down.

35:07.274 --> 35:08.959
Doesn't that leave the rock
vulnerable to Drill?

35:08.973 --> 35:11.275
Exactly, which is why
we don't have much time.

35:11.309 --> 35:15.279
Once all the magnets are turned,
reattach the wires.

35:15.313 --> 35:18.115
I'll activate the E.M.P.
and destroy the rock.

35:22.887 --> 35:26.023
[Electricity crackling]

35:26.057 --> 35:28.859
[Whispering]

35:28.876 --> 35:31.161
[Lights buzzing]

35:31.212 --> 35:33.830
Must be a power surge.

35:40.571 --> 35:43.307
It's Drill. He's here.

35:43.370 --> 35:45.154
Yeah, I'm almost done with this one.

35:45.205 --> 35:46.739
- [Guns cock]
- Everyone down!

35:50.043 --> 35:51.493
[Electricity crackling]

35:52.746 --> 35:54.330
I have full authority here!

35:54.381 --> 35:55.331
[Both grunt]

35:55.382 --> 35:57.333
You don't know what you're doing!

35:57.384 --> 35:58.667
If it gets to that rock, we are all dead!

35:58.669 --> 36:01.587
We have our orders. We <i> will</i> shoot you.

36:01.638 --> 36:03.339
Stop! I <i> will</i> shoot you!

36:03.390 --> 36:05.391
[Crackling continues]

36:07.177 --> 36:08.427
[Grunts]

36:08.478 --> 36:10.145
Tully!

36:10.180 --> 36:13.348
- Stand down!
- Wes!

36:13.350 --> 36:15.017
No one shoot.

36:15.051 --> 36:18.270
[Whispering]

36:18.321 --> 36:21.406
[Pulsing]

36:24.744 --> 36:27.696
No!

36:29.543 --> 36:31.641
- Put down your weapons!
- Sir, we have orders!

36:31.741 --> 36:33.241
I am countermanding those orders.

36:33.292 --> 36:34.743
Evacuate the premises now.

36:35.491 --> 36:37.458
Go! Go!

36:37.493 --> 36:39.777
We need to go, too.

36:39.828 --> 36:42.447
We can't. This is our chance.
Drill's in the rock.

36:42.498 --> 36:45.533
Wes, we can end this,
get rid of Drill for good.

36:45.535 --> 36:48.703
- [Pulsing]
- [Whispering]

36:48.705 --> 36:51.205
Take her.

36:51.805 --> 36:53.939
What? Why?

36:55.692 --> 36:56.659
Sean.

36:56.691 --> 36:57.975
Claire, listen to me. I'll do this alone.

36:58.026 --> 36:59.727
- No. No, no, no.
- I forgave you.

36:59.778 --> 37:00.894
No.

37:00.896 --> 37:02.563
I forgive you.

37:03.865 --> 37:04.865
No.

37:04.899 --> 37:05.983
- Tell Henry I love him.
- No.

37:06.067 --> 37:07.034
Go.

37:07.068 --> 37:08.035
- No, please.
- Now!

37:08.069 --> 37:09.736
- Go! Go.
- No! No! No! No!

37:09.788 --> 37:11.705
Let me go!

37:11.739 --> 37:14.208
Let me go! Wes! Wes! Sean!

37:14.242 --> 37:15.826
[Whispering]

37:28.756 --> 37:32.392
[Whispering]

37:32.427 --> 37:34.394
[Crackling]

37:43.104 --> 37:46.773
[Glass shatters]

37:46.775 --> 37:49.276
[Both panting]

37:54.082 --> 37:55.532
What...

37:55.583 --> 37:58.201
[Grunts]

37:58.286 --> 38:00.620
Oh, God.

38:00.671 --> 38:02.622
[Breathing heavily]

38:15.603 --> 38:17.721
Sean: Claire?

38:17.772 --> 38:19.389
- Claire?
- Sean? Sean?

38:19.440 --> 38:21.725
- I'm here, Claire.
- Sean! Sean!

38:21.776 --> 38:22.726
- [Grunts]
- You're...

38:22.777 --> 38:25.278
- Oh, God.
- [Metal clanging]

38:25.313 --> 38:26.279
Okay.

38:26.314 --> 38:28.949
Sean. Oh.

38:28.983 --> 38:30.533
[Panting] We did it.

38:30.568 --> 38:32.118
We did it. He's gone.

38:32.153 --> 38:34.454
It's over.

38:34.488 --> 38:36.990
Okay.

38:37.041 --> 38:39.492
[Sobs]

38:39.494 --> 38:43.246
Okay, okay. [Sniffles]

38:43.297 --> 38:45.999
[Breathing heavily]

38:50.135 --> 38:52.803
I'm sorry.

38:53.235 --> 38:55.369
You were the only one
who could get me in here.

38:55.403 --> 38:58.539
You made the right choice.

38:58.573 --> 38:59.907
It's just the way it had to be.

38:59.909 --> 39:01.375
[Siren wailing]

39:01.409 --> 39:03.577
- The cavalry's coming.
- What do we do?

39:03.579 --> 39:05.245
This isn't something I can fix overnight.

39:05.247 --> 39:06.413
Until I do, you run.

39:06.464 --> 39:09.250
Wes, thank you.
Thank you. I know how this...

39:09.301 --> 39:10.584
that's not important right now.

39:10.635 --> 39:13.253
You have to... you have to go with him.

39:13.305 --> 39:14.838
Now, the parking lot is right there.

39:14.889 --> 39:15.890
[Keys jingle]

39:15.924 --> 39:17.558
You take my car, you turn the key,

39:17.592 --> 39:19.393
and you get the hell away from here.

39:19.427 --> 39:21.562
- Okay?
- [Wailing continues]

39:21.596 --> 39:22.680
Go.

39:22.731 --> 39:25.265
Go!

39:25.267 --> 39:26.600
[Exhales sharply]

39:26.602 --> 39:28.902
Oh, come on.

39:37.912 --> 39:39.863
[Crickets chirping]

39:39.914 --> 39:42.199
Jessup: I'm here. I'm at the house, sir.

39:42.250 --> 39:44.034
I'd like to know what I'm doing here.

39:44.085 --> 39:45.986
Frommer: You're there to pick up the kid.

39:48.022 --> 39:50.324
I'm sorry, sir. I don't follow.

39:50.358 --> 39:52.659
I believe my orders are loud and clear.

39:52.694 --> 39:55.829
Bennigan's son...
I want him in our custody.

40:11.312 --> 40:12.446
Minx?

40:12.480 --> 40:16.616
What... What are you doing?

40:16.651 --> 40:17.651
Drill's here.

40:17.653 --> 40:20.120
I told Drill you want something from him,

40:20.154 --> 40:22.322
and he said he wants something from you.

40:22.324 --> 40:24.791
[Sighs]

40:24.826 --> 40:28.128
Maybe you can make a deal.

